title: Bring It On Gainesville Criterium Series
CFL TT Holiday Morning Time Trials
Wrigley Ride Cycling Tour
description:
The 4th Annual Wrigley Ride is excited to announce it will have it’s own date for 2015. 

Historically part of the Velo Fest 3 day cycling festival, our committee locally decided that Bryan and all our fellow riders deserve a time of their own. We invite all those who have been affected by the loss of others on their bicycle to come and ride to remember February 21, 2015.

This year in an effort to up our ability to do more education and awareness, we have added a fundraising goal. For those who choose to try it out, you will receive a beautiful commemorative jersey by Primal Wear, to show your support of safer streets for all.

As for the ride experience, we are excited to have our event start and finish at Sykes and Cooper Farm. A family friendly venue with easy access to I-95.

We have decided to start the ride mid morning and add some fun “activities” for you along the way. Local music by the Red River Band, food from Smokin D's Bar B Que, brews from New Belgium Beer, and friendship await you at the end of your journey.

All registrations include fully supported ride with SAG and rest stops every 10-15 miles. Teams are encouraged and will have a designated area to gather and set up for the day. We are excited to have Tour de Cure volunteers staffing our rest stops!

All funds raised go to Velo Fest Community Initiative for projects that support the mission of  awareness to cyclists and non cyclists to create mutually beneficial roads. A portion of the proceeds will go to the Bryan B. Wrigley Scholarship at Newberry College, his alma mater and scholarship created by his family.

More about Velo Fest Community Initiative and Bryan’s Story can be found at www.wrigleyride.org
course:
We have decided to start the ride mid morning and add some fun “activities” for you along the way. Local music by the Red River Band, food from Smokin D's Bar B Que, brews from New Belgium Beer, and friendship await you at the end of your journey.

All routes begin and end at Sykes and Cooper Farm. 25k, 50k, 100k distance options available, and all routes will provide a stop at Bryan's Ghost Bike.
directions: Approximately 10 minutes west of I-95 off SR 207.

title: Gasparilla Criterium and Action Sports Festival
Southeast Regional Series: Race The Riviera Panama City Criterium & Wa
Tour de Ranch Gran Fondo
description: Hammer Down Multisport is proud to present the 19th Annual Tour de Ranch Saturday April 18th 2015. Ride the Gran Fondo, Medio Fondo, Piccolo Fondo, and Dirty Fondo thru the rolling hills of beautiful Northwest Florida.
course: The Gran Fondo Century will have four rest stops, Medio Fondo Metric Century and Dirty Fondo two rest stops and the 25 mile PiccoloFondo one rest stop at the half-way point. Rest stops will be fully stocked with plenty of fresh fruit, snacks, water and sports drink. SAG support for Gran Fondo, Dirty Fondo and Medio Fondo will be provided.
notes:
ALL TIMES ARE CENTRAL STANDARD TIME.

Gran Fondo and Dirty Fondo ride will start at 8am CST. Medio Fondo at 8:10am CST. Piccolo Fondo ride at 8:15am CST.

 

Please arrive by no later than 7:00am CST for packet pick-up. Walk-up registration will start at 6:30 am.

 

FRIDAY NIGHT PACKET PICKUP AND REGISTRATION:

April 17th, 2015 from 5-7 PM CST - Diego's Burrito Factory

Burritos, Beer and Bikes...pure AWESOMENESS!!

Diego's Burrito Factory

15514 Front Beach Road

Panama City Beach, FL 32413

title: Florida Masters State Track Championships
description:
This is the USA Cycling Masters State Track Championship. It features two days of racing. On Saturday AM 
Starting at 9:30 am, May 30, Sprint TT, then individual pursuit, then sprint heats through finals. 

Saturday PM. 
Starting at 7 pm Kilometer TT and scratch races 

Sunday AM
Starting at 9: 30 am Points Race, Team Sprint, and Team Pursuit
course: The Brian Piccolo Velodrome is 333.3 meter track with 30 degree banks.
registration: Riders can register on-site for this event, and opens 1 1/2 hours before each event.  $10 for individual races, and $20 for team events.
notes: USA Cycling rules apply.  Only USA Cycling annual license holders that have Florida listed as their residence on their license are eligible for the championship.

title: Gainesville Atlantic 75
description: 5 person teams ride from Gainesville to the Atlantic
registration: Teams must send or deliver entry to Swift Cycle, 607 W University Ave, Gainesville, FL 32601 by August 15th. Entry must include team members names, Category, and a bicycle part.

title: Wicked Awesome Racing CX Race Series
Sami's Bakery Race Series Under the Lights
Seminole Cyclefest
description: The event consists of three routes, 25/62/92 mile rides.  Online registration opens on June 1.  This ride is in support of the wounded Veterans at WIRED Athletes and the Seminole County Kids House for their fight against child abuse.
course: All three route are supported with a full rolling enclosure escort supplied by the Seminole County Sheriffs Office.  See more info at www.seminolecyclefest.com
registration: Registration opens on June 1 and online registration closes on Nov 6, 2015.  See event website.
directions: Address is Fort Mellon Park, Sanford Florida.

title: Cycle Depot Presents Rev Up & Race
description: The Rev Up & Race Speedway Criterium, commonly known as a crit, is a bike race that will take place on the Homestead-Miami Speedway during the Ride for the Cure® event. As cyclists take to the roads for the Cure®, Rev Up & Race participants will complete a series of laps around the speedway in a timed setting. As with most crits, the bike race will be held on a course entirely closed to traffic. This fun event is designed for the racer who wishes to support Susan G. Komen®Miami/Ft. Lauderdale in our efforts to end breast cancer forever
directions:
Homestead-Miami Speedway
1 Ralph Sanchez Speedway Blvd
Homestead, FL 33035

title: Swamp Cross
description: 6th Annual Swamp Cross presented by 352 Racing and Bikes & More.  This event is the 2015 CX State Championship for Florida.
course: The course features the most elevation gain per lap in Florida cyclocross series, the LegSmith sandpit, and of course, the Swamp Stairs.
registration: Advance register online through USA Cycling. Onsite registration available for additional fee.
notes: Bathrooms, picnic shelter, playground, and skatepark on site.
directions: I-75  exit 399. 2 miles SE to Hal Brady Recreation Complex (14300 NW 146 Terrace, Alachua, FL 32616)
